import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(x='distance', y='delay', data=data)
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between distance and delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='time', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['time'].mean(), color='red', label=f'Mean: {data["time"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of time taken for each trip?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].median()))
    plt.legend()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['hour'] = pd.to_datetime(data['hour'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce').dt.hour
    chart = sns.countplot(x='hour', data=data)
    chart.set(title='What is the distribution of trips taken during different hours of the day?')
    chart.set(xlabel='Hour of the day', ylabel='Number of trips')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
